OL,3,C'It's appalling': Disabled people who
OL,4,Ccan walk refused hospital transport
OL,6,FITV Granada Reports correspondent Tim
OL,7,FScott spoke to patients after their
OL,8,Ftransport to vital appointments was
OL,9,Fsuddenly stopped
OL,11,FA blind woman who relies on ambulance
OL,12,Ftransport to get medical treatments
OL,13,Fsays she is "appalled" after she was
OL,14,Ftold she no longer qualified for the
OL,15,Fservice - because she can walk.
OL,17,FJoanne Roberts, from the Wirral, has
OL,18,Fto visit Manchester Royal Infirmary
OL,19,Fevery three months for essential
OL,20,Fmonitoring following kidney and
OL,21,Fpancreas transplants.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/12
