OL,3,C'It's appalling': Disabled people who
OL,4,Ccan walk refused hospital transport
OL,6,FThe 60 mile trip is done via help from
OL,7,Fthe ambulance service as she is
OL,8,Fcompletely blind, something she says
OL,9,Fhas "never been a problem".
OL,11,FBut, now she has been told the
OL,12,Fservice, delivered by West Midlands
OL,13,FAmbulance Service (WMAS) across
OL,14,FCheshire, Warrington, and Wirral on
OL,15,Fbehalf of NHS Cheshire and Merseyside,
OL,16,Fis being stopped and she would need to
OL,17,Fmake her own way to her appointments.
OL,19,FJoanne received the phone call at the
OL,20,Fstart of November 2025.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/12
