OL,3,C'It's appalling': Disabled people who
OL,4,Ccan walk refused hospital transport
OL,6,F"When I rang up on the Monday morning
OL,7,Fthe woman was really upset," she said.
OL,9,F"She said 'I'm afraid you're no longer
OL,10,Fentitled to transport. The theory is
OL,11,Fif you can walk, whether assisted or
OL,12,Fon your own, you can make it to the
OL,13,Fhospital on your own'."
OL,15,FJoanne added: "The ruling's come out
OL,16,Fthat you've got to be either a cancer
OL,17,Fpatient, a dialysis patient, or in a
OL,18,Fwheelchair and then they will consider
OL,19,Ftaking you."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/12
