OL,3,C'It's appalling': Disabled people who
OL,4,Ccan walk refused hospital transport
OL,6,FA spokesperson for the West Midlands
OL,7,FAbulance Service said: "Due to the ICB
OL,8,Frefusing to pay the full cost of
OL,9,Fproviding the step in provision of the
OL,10,FPatient Transport Services contract in
OL,11,FCheshire, the Trust has had to tighten
OL,12,Fthe criteria by which patients are
OL,13,Fbeing accepted so that the costs do
OL,14,Fnot over-run. This was done in
OL,15,Fagreement with the ICB from 1 November.
OL,17,F"This mirrors the national PTS
OL,18,Fcriteria which prioritises renal and
OL,19,Foncology as the most critical cases.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/12
